A daily on-line meeting that focuses on reading and discussing topics related to alcoholism followed by an open discussion.  Open to all; everyone is welcome to attend.  Meets 5:30 pm EST daily, 7 days a week for 1 hour. 

Daily focus is as follows:  
Monday:  Beginner's Meeting on Steps 1, 2, & 3 or a reading from Living Sober; 
Tuesday:  A reading/share from As Bill Sees It; 
Wednesday: A reading/share from the Big Book; 
Thursday: A reading of one step (rotating) each week, with the last week of the month being a Tradition ; 
Friday:  Open discussion/Principal 1st Friday; Anniversary Night on 4th Friday; 
Saturday:  Speaker, Experience Strength and Hope (Speaker meeting); 
Sunday:  A reading/share from the Daily Reflections. 

No passcode required

Queer & Sober is a weekday virtual AA Meeting where all are welcome, and LGBTQIA+ folks with a desire to stop drinking can feel free to be themselves.

Monday — Queer and Sober: AA Big Book Meeting;
Tuesday — Queer and Sober: AA Discussion Meeting with ASL Interpreter;
Wednesday — Queer and Sober: AA Beginner’s Meeting;
Thursday — Queer and Sober: AA Living Sober Meeting;
Friday — Queer and Sober: AA Steps 1-4 Discussion Meeting;

Same link every day.
